From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: V5 Project <v5@example.invalid>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 20:20:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] v5: keep cyclic reference clock errors out of RT logging

LinuxCNC-EtherCAT samples ecrt_master_reference_clock_time() from the 2 ms
realtime write function. The userspace library currently fprintfs every
failed ioctl before returning the errno, creating hundreds of synchronous
log writes per second when the DC datagram is temporarily unavailable. The
V5 lcec owner exports the fresh validity, success sequence, age, and error
count as HAL pins, so this cyclic API must only return the errno. Startup and
operator diagnostics consume those pins outside the realtime thread.
---
 lib/master.c | 2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/lib/master.c b/lib/master.c
index 2a9018e54..aa277e592 100644
--- a/lib/master.c
+++ b/lib/master.c
@@ -768,8 +768,6 @@ int ecrt_master_reference_clock_time(const ec_master_t *master,
 
     ret = ioctl(master->fd, EC_IOCTL_REF_CLOCK_TIME, time);
     if (EC_IOCTL_IS_ERROR(ret)) {
-        fprintf(stderr, "Failed to get reference clock time: %s\n",
-                strerror(EC_IOCTL_ERRNO(ret)));
         return -EC_IOCTL_ERRNO(ret);
     }
 
